title: Polish official wants Canada to extradite Ukrainian veteran of Nazi unit
description: Jewish groups said Yaroslav Hunka, who was lauded in Canada’s Parliament during a visit by President Zelensky, fought in a Nazi military unit during World War II.

title: Exodus from Nagorno-Karabakh accelerates; Azerbaijan arrests former leader
description: An exodus of Armenians from the disputed region of Nagorno-Karabakh accelerated on Wednesday and a top regional official was detained at the border.

title: Israelis can travel to U.S. without visa from Nov. 30
description: In return, Israel is dropping travel restrictions against Palestinian and Arab Americans.

title: U.S.-Israel visa deal could give some Palestinians new freedom of movement
description: The visa deal could have a major impact on Palestinian Americans, whom Israel must now treat like other American citizens when they enter the country.

title: North Korea announces expulsion of Travis King, U.S. soldier who defected
description: Travis King had been punished for misconduct while serving in South Korea and was being sent home to the United States when he crossed the border.

title: In photos: Iraq wedding fire in Nineveh kills at least 100
description: A fire at a wedding hall in Iraq’s Nineveh province killed at least 100 people and injured 150 on Wednesday.

title: Ukraine live briefing: Russia cites video to claim admiral supposedly killed by Ukraine is alive
description: Footage posted by Russia’s Defense Ministry on Tuesday that appears to show Adm. Viktor Sokolov alive and attending a videoconference has raised questions.

title: Old-style camera once banned by the Taliban captures a new Afghan reality
description: Rodrigo Abd, a photographer with the Associated Press, traveled across Afghanistan with a wooden box camera known as a kamra-e-faoree.

title: Trump’s favorite European leader does Russia’s work in Europe
description: The bonhomie between Hungarian Prime Minister Viktor Orban and former president Donald Trump is just the tip of the spear of a broader ideological alliance.

title: Fire at Iraqi wedding hall kills at least 100, injures 150
description: At least 100 people were killed and 150 injured after a fire broke out at a wedding in Iraq’s Nineveh province, according to local media reports.

title: 8 killed by electrocution in South Africa’s flooded informal settlements
description: Eight people, including four children, were fatally electrocuted in poor townships where residents precariously hook their own homes up to the grid.
